[[[break]]]added at line 25: *lime {code 
*pink In my limited experience of what scientists do, experimentalists are directed by theoreticians. Someone comes up with a theory, other people engage in experiments to prove or disprove it.

Normatively I think this is a very good idea. It's simply more efficient to target experiments at a theory, rather than blindly stumble into experiments and knit together a theory around them.

Regarding a ToE, I think it's both plausible and desirable for Einstein to be right. Plausible because countless times humans have come to gaps knowledge, and countless times we've filled them. When we arrive at a new gap it would be unusual to say _'oh no! It's gap, what ever shall will we do?!'_ 

It's desirable because, as an inquisitive human, I don't much like gaps in knowledge. Also it gives me good cause to bite my thumb at theists. Offending people, descriptively, makes me happy*

Greg.Sadler
}*
